        {
            "id": "combining_loops_and_checking",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can combine loops and the `in` operator to do powerful things."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Lets say you have a list of `available` fruits and a list of `wanted` fruits. You can loop through the `wanted` items and check if each item is in the `available` list."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "available = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"orange\"]\nwanted = [\"banana\", \"grape\", \"apple\"]\n\nfor item in wanted:\n    if item in available:\n        print(f\"{item} is available!\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"{item} is not available.\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "banana is available!\ngrape is not available.\napple is available!"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
